 }}\n* {{cite book |last = Schram |first = Stuart |author-link = Stuart R. Schram |title = Mao Tse-Tung |year = 1966 |publisher = Simon & Schuster |location = |isbn = 978-0140208405 |ref = CITEREFSchram1966 |url-access = registration |url = https://archive.org/details/maotsetung0000schr }}\n* {{cite book |last = Shambaugh |first = David |ref = CITEREFShambaugh2008 |title = China's Communist Party: Atrophy and Adaptation |publisher = [[University of California Press]] |year = 2008 |isbn = 978-0520254923 |author-link = David Shambaugh }}\n* {{cite book |last = Shambaugh |first = David |ref = CITEREFShambaugh2013 |title = China Goes Global: The Partial Power |publisher = Oxford University Press |year = 2013 |isbn = 978-0199323692 }}\n* {{cite book |last = Sullivan |first = Lawrence |ref = CITEREFSullivan2007 |title = Historical Dictionary of the People's Republic of China |publisher = Scarecrow Press |year = 2007 |isbn = 978-0810864436 }}\n* {{cite book |last = Sullivan |first = Lawrence |ref = CITEREFSullivan2012 |title = Historical Dictionary of the Chinese Communist Party |publisher = Scarecrow Press |year = 2012 |isbn = 978-0810872257 }}\n* {{cite book |last = Jonathan |first = Unger |author-link = Jonathan Unger |ref = CITEREFUnger2002 |title = The Nature of Chinese Politics: From Mao to Jiang |publisher = M.E. Sharpe |year = 2002 |isbn = 978-0765641151 }}\n* {{cite book |last = van de Ven |first = Johan |author-link = Hans van de Ven |ref = CITEREFVan_de_Ven1991 |title = From Friend to Comrade: The Founding of the Chinese Communist Party, 1920\u20131927 |url = https://archive.org/details/fromfriendtocomr00vand |url-access = registration |publisher = University of California Press |year = 1991 |isbn = 978-0520910874 }}\n* {{cite book |last =  Vogel |first = Ezra |author-link = Ezra Vogel |ref = CITEREFVogel2011 |title = Deng Xiaoping and the Transformation of China |publisher = Harvard University Press |year = 2011 |isbn = 978-0674055445 }}\n* {{cite book |last = Yeh |first = Wen-hsin |ref = CITEREFYeh1996 |title = Provincial Passages: Culture, Space, and the Origins of Chinese Communism |url = https://archive.org/details/provincialpassag0000yehw |url-access = registration |publisher = [[University of California Press]] |year = 1996 |isbn = 978-0520916326 }}\n* {{cite book |last1 = Wang |first1 = Gunwu |last2 = Zheng |first2 = Yongian |ref = CITEREFWangZheng2012 |title = China: Development and Governance |publisher = World Scientific |year = 2012 |isbn = 978-9814425834 }}\n* {{cite book |last = White |first = Stephen |ref = CITEREFWhite2000 |title = Russia's New Politics: The Management of a Postcommunist Society |publisher = Cambridge University Press |year = 2000 |isbn = 978-0521587372 }}\n* {{cite book |last = Wong |first = Yiu-chung |ref = CITEREFWong2005 |title = From Deng Xiaoping to Jiang Zemin: Two Decades of Political Reform in the People's Republic of China |publisher = University Press of America |year = 2005 |isbn = 978-0761830740 }}\n* {{cite book |last = Zheng |first = Suisheng |ref = CITEREFZheng2004 |title = A Nation-state by Construction: Dynamics of Modern Chinese Nationalism |publisher = Stanford University Press |year = 2004 |isbn = 978-0804750011 }}\n{{refend}}\n\n== External links ==\n{{Library resources box}}\n{{Commons and category|Communist Party of China}}\n* {{official website|http://english.cpc.people.com.cn/}}\n* [http://english.peopledaily.com.cn ''People's Daily''], official newspaper of the [[CPC Central Committee]]\n\n{{-}}\n{{Communist Party of China}}\n{{Navboxes\n|list =\n{{People's Republic of China politics}}\n{{PRC political parties}}\n{{Warlord era}}\n{{Chinese Civil War}}\n{{Cold War}}\n{{Eastern Bloc parties}}\n}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Communist Party Of China}}\n[[Category:Communist Party of China| ]]\n[[Category:Communist parties in China]]\n[[Category:Ruling Communist parties]]\n[[Category:Political parties established in 1921]]\n[[Category:Political parties in the Republic of China]]\n[[Category:Chinese Civil War]]\n[[Category:Maoist parties]]\n[[Category:Government of China]]\n[[Category:1921 establishments in China]]\n[[Category:Parties of one-party systems]]\n[[Category:Chinese nationalist political parties]]\n", "name_user": "Wjjefferies", "label": "unsafe", "comment": "", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Communist_Party_of_China"}
{"title_page": "List of current champions in WWE", "text_new": "{{pp-semi|small=yes}}\n{{short description|Listing of championships currently utilized by American professional wrestling promotion WWE}}\n{{use mdy dates|date=October 2018}}\n[[WWE]] is an American [[professional wrestling]] [[Professional wrestling promotion|promotion]] based out of [[Stamford, Connecticut|Stamford]], [[Connecticut]]. Title reigns are either determined by [[Professional wrestling match types|professional wrestling matches]] or are awarded to a wrestler, as a result of the culmination of various scripted [[Kayfabe|storylines]].\n\nWWE promotes three primary [[WWE brand extension|brands]] \u2013 [[Raw (WWE brand)|Raw]], [[SmackDown (WWE brand)|SmackDown]], and [[NXT (WWE brand)|NXT]].<ref>[http://www.wwe.com/shows/wwenxt/article/nxt-moves-to-usa-network NXT moves to USA Network - WWE.com]</ref> Specialty brands in WWE include [[205 Live (WWE brand)|205 Live]] \u2013 for male wrestlers 205 lbs. and under (designated by WWE as [[Cruiserweight (professional wrestling)|cruiserweights]]) \u2013 and [[NXT UK (WWE brand)|NXT UK]], which is for wrestlers based in the [[United Kingdom]].\n\nRaw, SmackDown, and NXT each have a primary and secondary championship for male wrestlers, a singles championship for female wrestlers, and a tag team championship for male wrestlers. There is also one tag team championship for female wrestlers that is shared between the three brands. There is one championship for the cruiserweight wrestlers that is shared between NXT, NXT UK, and 205 Live, which is the only championship with a weight limit in the promotion, and one male singles, one female singles, and one male tag team championship for NXT UK wrestlers. There is also one tertiary championship, which is accessible to anyone, regardless of gender or WWE status.\n\nThere are currently 18 championships in WWE. Among the five current brands, 23 wrestlers hold the championships as of {{CURRENTMONTHNAME}} {{CURRENTDAY}}, {{CURRENTYEAR}}. The list includes the number of times the wrestler has held the title, the date and location of the win, and a description of the winning bout.\n\n== Current champions ==\n; Men's singles\nAt the top of [[WWE]]'s championship hierarchy for male wrestlers are the [[WWE Championship]] on [[Raw (WWE brand)|Raw]], the [[WWE Universal Championship|Universal Championship]] on [[SmackDown (WWE brand)|SmackDown]], and the [[NXT Championship]] on [[NXT (WWE brand)|NXT]] \u2014 all designated as [[Professional wrestling championship#World championships|world championships]]. The WWE Champion is [[Brock Lesnar]], who is in his fifth reign. He won the title by defeating [[Kofi Kingston]] during ''[[SmackDown's 20th Anniversary]]'' on October 4, 2019.<ref>{{cite web|title=WWE Championship|url=http://www.wwe.com/classics/titlehistory/wwe-championship|publisher=[[WWE]]|accessdate=January 3, 2020}}</ref> The Universal Championship is held by [[Braun Strowman]], who is in his first reign. He won the title by defeating [[Bill Goldberg|Goldberg]] on night one of [[WrestleMania 36]] on April 4, 2020 (taped March 25, 2020).<ref>{{cite web|title=Universal Championship|url=http://www.wwe.com/classics/titlehistory/universal-championship|publisher=[[WWE]]|accessdate=January 3, 2020}}</ref> The NXT Championship is held by [[Adam Cole]], who is in his first reign. He won the title by defeating [[Johnny Gargano]] at [[NXT TakeOver: XXV|TakeOver: XXV]] on June 1, 2019.<ref>{{cite web|title=NXT Championship|url=http://www.wwe.com/classics/titlehistory/nxt-championship|publisher=[[WWE]]|accessdate=January 3, 2020}}</ref>\n\n[[Professional wrestling championship#Location-specific championships|Secondary titles]] for male wrestlers include the [[WWE United States Championship|United States Championship]] on Raw, the [[WWE Intercontinental Championship|Intercontinental Championship]] on SmackDown, and the [[NXT North American Championship]] on NXT. The United States Championship is held by [[Andrade Cien Almas|Andrade]], who is in his first reign. He won the title by defeating [[Rey Mysterio]] at a [[WWE Live]] event on December 26, 2019.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.wwe.com/classics/titlehistory/unitedstates/|title=United States Championship|publisher=[[WWE]]|accessdate=January 3, 2020}}</ref> The Intercontinental Championship is held by [[Sami Zayn]], who is in his first reign. He won the title by defeating [[Braun Strowman]] in a [[Handicap match|3-on-1 Handicap match]] also featuring [[Cesaro (wrestler)|Cesaro]] and [[Shinsuke Nakamura]] as Zayn's partners on  March 8, 2020 at [[Elimination Chamber (2020)|Elimination Chamber]]\u2014Zayn won the title since he pinned Strowman. The North American Championship is held by first-time title holder [[Keith Lee (wrestler)|Keith Lee]], who defeated [[Roderick Strong]] on the January 22, 2020 episode of ''[[WWE NXT|NXT]]''.<ref>{{cite web|title=NXT North American Championship|url=http://www.wwe.com/classics/titlehistory/nxt-north-american-championship|publisher=[[WWE]]|accessdate=January 3, 2020}}</ref>\n\n; Men's tag team\n[[World tag team championship|Tag team championships]] for male wrestlers include the [[WWE Raw Tag Team Championship|Raw Tag Team Championship]], the [[WWE SmackDown Tag Team Championship|SmackDown Tag Team Championship]], and the [[NXT Tag Team Championship]]. The Raw Tag Team Championship is held by [[The Street Profits]] (Angelo Dawkins and Montez Ford), who are in their first reign as a team and individually. They won the title by defeating [[Seth Rollins]] and [[Buddy Murphy|Murphy]] in a [[Professional wrestling match types#Last Chance match|Now or Never match]] on the March 2, 2020 episode of ''[[Monday Night Raw]]''.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.wwe.com/classics/titlehistory/raw-tag-team-championship|title=Raw Tag Team Championship|publisher=[[WWE]]|accessdate=January 3, 2020}}</ref> The SmackDown Tag Team Championship is held by [[The Miz and John Morrison]], who are in their first reign as a team and second for [[The Miz]] individually. They won the titles by defeating [[The New Day (professional wrestling)|The New Day]]'s [[Big E (wrestler)|Big E]] and [[Kofi Kingston]] at [[Super ShowDown (2020)|Super ShowDown]] on February 27, 2020. The NXT Tag Team Championship is held by The BroserWeights ([[Matt Riddle]] and [[Pete Dunne]]), who are in their first reign. They defeated [[The Undisputed Era]]'s [[Bobby Fish]] and [[Kyle O'Reilly]] at [[NXT TakeOver: Portland|TakeOver: Portland]] on February 16, 2020.\n\n; Specialty\nThe [[WWE 24/7 Championship]] is a tertiary championship shared across all five brands and is open to anyone regardless of gender (including non-WWE personnel). It can be defended anytime, [[Falls Count Anywhere match|anywhere]], as long as a WWE referee is present. The current champion is [[Mojo Rawley]], who is in his seventh reign. He won the title by pinning [[R-Truth]] on a pillar at night one of [[WrestleMania 36]].\n\nThe [[NXT Cruiserweight Championship]] is the only championship of the [[205 Live (WWE brand)|205 Live]] brand and is also defended on NXT and NXT UK. It is for wrestlers {{convert|205|lb|kg|abbr=on}} and under (referred to as [[Cruiserweight (professional wrestling)|cruiserweights]]); the only championship in WWE with a [[Professional wrestling championship#Weight class championships|weight limit]]. The title is held by [[Jordan Devlin]], who is in his first reign. He won the title by defeating former champion [[Angel Garza]], [[Travis Banks]], and [[Isaiah \"Swerve\" Scott]], who Devlin pinned, in a [[fatal four-way match]] at [[Worlds Collide (2020)|Worlds Collide]] on January 25, 2020.<ref>{{cite web|title=NXT Cruiserweight Championship|url=http://www.wwe.com/classics/titlehistory/nxt-cruiserweight-championship|publisher=[[WWE]]|accessdate=January 3, 2020}}</ref>\n\n; Women's\nAt the top of WWE's championship hierarchy for female wrestlers are the [[WWE Raw Women's Championship|Raw Women's Championship]], the [[WWE SmackDown Women's Championship|SmackDown Women's Championship]], and the [[NXT Women's Championship]] \u2014 all designated as world championships. The Raw Women's Championship is held by [[Becky Lynch]], who is in her first reign. She won the title in a [[Professional wrestling match types#Winner Takes All match|Winner Takes All]] [[Professional wrestling match types#Basic non-elimination matches|triple threat match]] involving former champion [[Ronda Rousey]] and [[Charlotte Flair]] (who defended the SmackDown Women's Championship) at [[WrestleMania 35]] on April 8, 2019.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.wwe.com/classics/titlehistory/raw-womens-championship|title=Raw Women's Championship|publisher=[[WWE]]|accessdate=January 3, 2020}}</ref> The SmackDown Women's Championship is held by [[Bayley (wrestler)|Bayley]], who is in her second reign. She won the title by defeating [[Charlotte Flair]] on ''[[SmackDown]]'' on October 11, 2019.<ref>{{cite web|title=SmackDown Women's Championship|url=http://www.wwe.com/classics/titlehistory/smackdown-womens-championship|publisher=[[WWE]]|accessdate=January 3, 2020}}</ref> The NXT Women's Championship is held by [[Rhea Ripley]], who is in her first reign. She won the title by defeating [[Shayna Baszler]] on the December 18, 2019 episode of ''[[WWE NXT|NXT]]''.<ref>{{cite web|title=NXT Women's Championship|url=http://www.wwe.com/classics/titlehistory/nxt-womens-championship|publisher=[[WWE]]|accessdate=January 3, 2020}}</ref>\n\nThe [[WWE Women's Tag Team Championship|Women's Tag Team Championship]] is the only tag team championship for female wrestlers in WWE, and is shared between the Raw, SmackDown, and NXT brands.<ref name=\"AllBrands\">{{cite web|url=https://www.wwe.com/shows/raw/article/wwe-womens-tag-team-championships-defend-raw-smackdown-live-nxt|title=WWE Women\u2019s Tag Team Championships to be defended across Raw, SmackDown LIVE and NXT|date=February 18, 2019|last=Benigno|first=Anthony|work=WWE.com|accessdate=February 19, 2019}}</ref> It is held by [[Alexa Bliss]] and [[Nikki Cross]] from SmackDown, who are in their second reign. They won the title by defeating The Kabuki Warriors [[Asuka (wrestler)|Asuka]] and [[Kairi Sane]] on night one of [[WrestleMania 36]] on April 4, 2020 (taped March 25, 2020).<ref>{{cite web|title=WWE Women's Tag Team Championship|url=http://www.wwe.com/classics/titlehistory/wwe-womens-tag-team-championship|publisher=[[WWE]]|accessdate=January 3, 2020}}</ref> \n\n; UK\nThe top title of [[NXT UK (WWE brand)|NXT UK]] is the [[NXT United Kingdom Championship]]. It is held by [[Walter (wrestler)|Walter]], who is in his first reign. He won the title by defeating [[Pete Dunne (wrestler)|Pete Dunne]] at [[NXT TakeOver: New York|TakeOver: New York]] on April 5, 2019, ending Dunne's reign at 685 days.<ref>{{cite web|title=WWE United Kingdom Championship|url=http://www.wwe.com/classics/titlehistory/wwe-united-kingdom-championship|publisher=[[WWE]]|accessdate=January 3, 2020}}</ref> The [[NXT UK Women's Championship]] is held by first-time title holder [[Kay Lee Ray]], who won the title by defeating [[Toni Storm]] at [[NXT UK TakeOver: Cardiff|TakeOver: Cardiff]] on August 31, 2019.<ref>{{cite web|title=NXT UK Women's Championship|url=http://www.wwe.com/classics/titlehistory/nxt-uk-womens-championship|publisher=[[WWE]]|accessdate=January 3, 2020}}</ref> The [[NXT UK Tag Team Championship]] is held by Gallus ([[Mark Coffey]] and [[Wolfgang (wrestler)|Wolfgang]]), who are in their first reign.  They defeated [[Mark Andrews (wrestler)|Mark Andrews]] and [[Morgan Webster|Flash Morgan Webster]] on October 4, 2019 during the ''[[NXT UK]]'' tapings ([[Broadcast delay|aired]] October 17).<ref>{{cite web|title=NXT UK Tag Team Championship|url=http://www.wwe.com/classics/titlehistory/nxt-uk-tag-team-championship|publisher=[[WWE]]|accessdate=January 3, 2020}}</ref>\n\n=== Raw ===\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"font-size: 85%;\"\n|-\n!Championship\n!colspan=2 | Current champion(s)\n!Reign\n!Date won \n!Days<br />held\n!Location\n!Notes\n|-\n|align=center | [[WWE Championship]]\n|align=center | [[File:Brock Lesnar WWE Champion 2014.jpg|100px]]\n|align=center | [[Brock Lesnar]]\n|align=center | 5\n|align=center | October 4, 2019\n|align=center | {{age in days|month1=10|day1=04|year1=2019}}\n|align=center | [[Los Angeles, California]]\n|Defeated [[Kofi Kingston]] on ''[[WWE SmackDown's 20th Anniversary|SmackDown's 20th Anniversary]]''.<br><small>On the November 1, 2019 episode of ''[[WWE SmackDown|SmackDown]]'', Lesnar quit the [[SmackDown (WWE brand)|SmackDown brand]] and went to the [[Raw (WWE brand)|Raw brand]], taking the title with him.</br>\n|-\n| align=\"center\" | [[Raw Women's Championship]]\n| align=\"center\" | [[File:Becky_Lynch_July_2019.jpg|alt=|100px]]\n| align=\"center\" | [[Becky Lynch]]\n| align=\"center\" | 1\n| align=\"center\" | April 8, 2019\n| align=\"center\" | {{age in days|month1=4|day1=8|year1=2019}}\n| align=\"center\" | [[East Rutherford, New Jersey]]\n|Defeated previous champion [[Ronda Rousey]] and [[Charlotte Flair]] at [[WrestleMania 35]] in a [[Winner Takes All match|winner takes all]] [[triple threat match]] in which Flair also defended her [[SmackDown Women's Championship]].\n|-\n| align=\"center\" | [[WWE United States Championship|United States Championship]]\n| align=\"center\" | [[File:Manny Andrade NXT Takeover Dallas 2016.jpg|alt=|100px]]\n| align=\"center\" | [[Andrade Cien Almas|Andrade]]\n| align=\"center\" | 1\n| align=\"center\" | December 26, 2019\n| align=\"center\" | {{age in days|month1=12|day1=26|year1=2019}}\n| align=\"center\" | [[New York, New York|New York City, New York]]\n|Defeated [[Rey Mysterio]] at a [[WWE Live]] event.\n|-\n| align=\"center\" | [[Raw Tag Team Championship]]\n| align=\"center\" | [[File:Dawkins_and_Ford.jpg|100px]]\n| align=\"center\" |[[The Street Profits]]<br>{{small|(Angelo Dawkins and Montez Ford)}}\n| align=\"center\" | 1\